    caption: [The crowded structure of the cell interior. Only the macromolecules, which are drawn to scale and displayed in different colors, are shown. Enzymes and MBoC7 e3.22/2.27 other macromolecules diffuse relatively slowly inside the cell, in part because they interact with many other macromolecules; small molecules, by contrast, diffuse nearly as rapidly as they do in water (Movie 2.4). (From S.R. McGuffee and A.H. Elcock, PLoS Comput. Biol. 6(3):e1000694, 2010.)],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
