  "2-62": (
    caption: [Glycolysis and the citric acid cycle are at the center of an elaborate set of metabolic pathways in human cells. Some 2000 metabolic reactions are shown schematically with the reactions of glycolysis and the citric acid cycle in red. Many other reactions either lead into these two central pathways—delivering small molecules to be catabolized with production of energy— or they lead outward as in Figure 2–60 to supply carbon compounds for the purpose of biosynthesis. (Adapted from KEGG Database. With permission from Kanehisa Laboratories.)],
